definition: located at/set up in a particular location
to set up/to arrange/to establish/to found/to display
(located) at/(to be) in/to exist/in the middle of doing sth/(indicating an action in progress)

sentences.english: The company's headquarter is located in Jinhua city and the company has its own customs broker.
sentences.chinese: 公司总部设在金华，并有自己的报关行。

sentences.english: Existing staff of 50 people, the plant located in the east village Humen.
sentences.chinese: 现有员工五十余人，总厂设在虎门东风村。

sentences.english: Amylin is headquartered in San Diego, California.
sentences.chinese: 胰淀素是总部设在加利福尼亚州圣迭戈。

sentences.english: The command post was set up in a forward position.
sentences.chinese: 指挥部设在前沿阵地上。

sentences.english: His headquarters are somewhere in the Everglades, his gang are a mixed-up bunch.
sentences.chinese: 其总部设在某处沼泽地，他的团伙是一个混合了一堆。

sentences.english: The novel is set in a futureworld.
sentences.chinese: 小说的背景设在未来世界。

sentences.english: The company is headquartered at No. 3 Nanhuan Road, Zhoutie Town, Southwest Suburb, Wuxi.

sentences.english: Please go to the Shanghai Travel Service Agency in our hotel.

sentences.english: The factory address is located in Long Huahe the back industrial district, has the staff more than 200 people.

sentences.english: An optional bow member clips about the pinna.

sentences.english: The head office of the Group after its mergence is located in Beijing.

sentences.english: Headquartered in lanzhou city, gansu province.

sentences.english: The team's field headquarters that night would be an empty building on the very edge of town.

sentences.english: Our company situates in Shenzhen for foreign business contact.

sentences.english: Home at the place far away from downtown area.

sentences.english: Neal Communities is based in Manatee County.

definition: to set up/to arrange/to establish/to found/to display
to set up separately/to establish separate units
to be located at/to be situated at/to lie
